UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1271
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of the victims
2 of the United Parcel Service Airlines Flight 2976, and commending those who responded
3 to the incident.
4 WHEREAS, on November 4, 2025, at around 5:13 p.m., United Parcel Service
5 (UPS) Airlines Flight 2976, a cargo flight from Louisville Muhammad Ali International
6 Airport to Honolulu, Hawaii, suffered a separation of its left engine during its takeoff roll
7 and crashed into an industrial area seconds after liftoff from the runway; and
8 WHEREAS, the ensuing crash killed 15 people, including all three crew members
9 on board the aircraft, and resulted in injuries to 22 other individuals; and
10 WHEREAS, those killed in the disaster included the flight crew: Captain Dana
11 Diamond, 62; Captain Richard Wartenberg, 57; and First Officer Lee Truitt, 45; and
12 those who perished on the ground: Angela Anderson, 45; Carlos Fernandez, 52; Louisnes
13 Fedon, 47; Kimberly Asa, 3; Trinadette "Trina" Chavez, 37; Tony Crain, 65; John
14 Loucks, 52; John Spray, 45; Matthew Sweets, 37; Ella Petty Whorton, 31; Megan
15 Washburn, 35; and Alain Rodriguez Colina, 50; and
16 WHEREAS, when speaking of those lost, Louisville Metro Mayor Craig Greenberg
17 said, "Today, as we share the names of those who we lost, our city feels the full weight of
18 this unimaginable tragedy. Behind every one of these names is a circle of family, friends,
19 stories that will forever be unfinished."; and
20 WHEREAS, this incident was devastating to the entire community of Louisville,
21 where UPS is the largest employer in the city, and whose Worldport global air hub is the
22 third largest air cargo hub in the nation; and
23 WHEREAS, in the immediate aftermath of the crash, fire departments, law
24 enforcement agencies, emergency medical services departments, and other agencies
25 worked tirelessly in cooperation to secure the crash site, put out massive fires, search for
26 victims, and tend to those in need; and
27 WHEREAS, in addition to the Louisville Fire Department and the Louisville
