1 Airport Authority Fire Department, fire departments from Shively, Anchorage-
2 Middletown, St. Matthews, Fern Creek, Jeffersontown, Okolona Fire, Fairdale, Pleasure
3 Ridge Park, Shepherdsville, Zoneton, Lexington/Fayette County, the Kentucky Air
4 National Guard, Mount Washington, Nichols, Lebanon Junction, Southeast Bullitt
5 County, Simpsonville, Bardstown, Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport,
6 Marathon Oil, and Utica, Indiana, supplied staff and equipment and endeavored to put out
7 the fires, search for survivors, and recover those killed; and
8 WHEREAS, similarly, the Louisville Metro Police Department and the Louisville
9 Airport Authority Police Department enlisted the aid of agencies such as the Jefferson
10 County Sheriff's Office, Audubon Park Police, Middletown Police, St. Matthews Police,
11 University of Louisville Police, Louisville Alcoholic Beverage Control, Kentucky State
12 Police, the Louisville Offices of the Federal Bureau of Investigation and Bureau of
13 Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives, the Louisville Fire Arson Bureau, Jefferson
14 County Coroner's Office, and the National Transportation Safety Board; and
15 WHEREAS, medical services and care were provided by emergency medical
16 services crews from Louisville Metro, Anchorage-Middletown, St. Matthews, Fern
17 Creek, Jeffersontown, Okolona, Pleasure Ridge Park, Bullitt County, Ameripro, and
18 Heartland, as well as the University of Louisville Hospital emergency department; and
19 WHEREAS, the unique nature of this tragedy required more than just efforts from
20 traditional first responders, and further assistance and aid was provided by Louisville
21 Metro Government, the Kentucky Governor's Office, the Metropolitan Sewer District,
22 Louisville Metro Emergency Management, the American Synthetic Rubber/Michelin
23 Emergency Response Team, the Dow Chemical Fire Brigade, the National Weather
24 Service, the Transit Authority of River City, the Kentucky Division of Emergency
25 Management, the Kentucky and Louisville Departments of Public Health, the Federal
26 Aviation Administration Louisville Office, the Kentucky Urban Search and Rescue Task
27 Force, and the Louisville Water Company; and
