BR127100.100 - 1271 - XXXX 1/8/2026 4:46 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1271
1 WHEREAS, while a city and a Commonwealth remember and mourn for those lost
2 in this tragedy, we can remember that our response to this crash was an overwhelming
3 desire to help, and to do what was necessary without question to address all the problems
4 that come from a disaster of this magnitude;
5 NOW, THEREFORE,
6 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
7 Kentucky:
8 Section 1. The members of the Senate join with Senator Keturah Herron in
9 remembering the victims of UPS Airlines Flight 2976, praying for comfort for their
10 families, as well as those injured in the crash, and recognizing the efforts of the first
11 responders and other agencies who responded to this disaster.
12 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in loving memory and
13 honor of the victims of UPS Airlines Flight 2976.
14 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit copies of this
15 Resolution to Senator Keturah Herron for delivery to the victims' families and the
16 responding agencies.
